description: To understand the importance of the JFK files, we need to go back to the man himself. John F. Kennedy was more than just a president—he was a symbol, a paradox, and in many ways, a myth. He was a war hero, yet his family’s wealth and influence had insulated him from the struggles of ordinary Americans. He was a devout Catholic, yet his personal life was a whirlwind of extramarital affairs, including a rumored relationship with Marilyn Monroe. He was a Cold War warrior, taking America to the brink of nuclear war during the Cuban Missile Crisis, yet he spoke of peace and sought diplomacy with the Soviet Union. For many Americans, Kennedy was the embodiment of youthful optimism, of a nation on the cusp of greatness. But behind the glamour of Camelot, there were shadows—secrets within his administration, tensions with intelligence agencies, and enemies both at home and abroad.
title: JFK Files: Will we finally learn truth about Marilyn Monroe or Cuba?

At the Raisina Dialogue, he discussed historical injustices, particularly citing the Kashmir issue as an example, and called for a review of global governance frameworks to acknowledge evolving power dynamics.
title: 'Attacker, victim were put on par': Jaishankar takes a jibe at UN, cites Kashmir

description: The National Board of Examination in Medical Sciences (NBEMS) has announced that NEET PG 2025 will be conducted in two shifts on June 15, sparking concerns among aspirants. Candidates have taken to X (formerly Twitter) to criticize the move, recalling issues with last year’s normalization process and expressing worries about the potential challenges of holding the exam in multiple shifts.
title: Candidates call NEET PG 2025 in two shifts a 'flawed decision,' demand a single-shift exam

description: Ford has finalised plans to repurpose its Chennai facility to manufacture and export engines, excluding vehicle production in India. The initiative aligns with Ford's global strategy and follows the company's exit from vehicle manufacturing in India in 2021.
title: Ford may export engines out of Chennai plant

description: Nasa astronaut Sunita Williams and her crew will return to Earth aboard the SpaceX Crew Dragon capsule after spending nine months in space. Their return, initially planned for Wednesday, has been moved up to Tuesday due to weather concerns, with a planned splashdown off the coast of Florida.
title: Sunita Williams heads to Earth: How and where she will land, when and where to watch

description: NASA astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore are set to return from the ISS after a nine-month mission, extended due to technical challenges with the Starliner spacecraft. Williams advocated against SpaceX CEO Elon Musk’s call to decommission the ISS early, emphasizing its ongoing contribution to scientific research. Musk suggested deorbiting within two years to focus on deep-space exploration.
title: Elon Musk wants ISS gone, Sunita Williams pushes boundaries for it's retirement

description: When it comes to MS Dhoni these days, the start of every IPL is speculation time. Will this finally be his last season? Is he still sharp as a keeper? Can his body take the wear & tear? Apart from the brand value, is he still relevant in CSK’s scheme of things? For his legions of fans, though, these things don’t matter. Their hero’s presence on the field is enough.
title: IPL 2025: MS Dhoni love story, to be continued at CSK

description: WWE RAW in Belgium featured the return of John Cena as a heel, explosive matches, and chaotic conclusions. Highlights included Cena's confrontation with Cody Rhodes, Penta defeating Ludwig Kaiser, and a dramatic Intercontinental Championship match where Bron Breakker retained his title amidst interference and assault.
title: WWE RAW Results and Highlights (3/17/25): John Cena Returns to End Relationship with Fans

description: The Israeli government, in coordination with the US administration, launched a significant airstrike on Hamas positions in Gaza, resulting in at least 69 Palestinian casualties. The operation is in response to stalled ceasefire negotiations, with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu authorizing the strikes.
title: Did Israel consult US before Gaza airstrikes? White House responds

description: Punjab Kings have revamped their team and appointed Shreyas Iyer as captain, aiming for their first-ever IPL title. One of their key retained players, Prabhsimran Singh, is hopeful that Iyer's leadership will bring luck and success to the team in the 2025 season.
title: EXCLUSIVE | Shreyas Iyer will be our 'lucky charm': Prabhsimran

description: Bangladesh's interim government has strongly protested against US intelligence chief Tulsi Gabbard's comments on minority persecution, calling them misleading and damaging. The government emphasized its fight against extremism and urged Gabbard to base her remarks on facts to avoid stoking sectarian tensions.
title: 'Misleading': Bangladesh slams Tulsi Gabbard remark on minority persecution

description: Rishabh Pant recreated the viral clip of Sunil Gavaskar shouting 'stupid, stupid, stupid' during commentary when the Indian wicketkeeper-batter threw away his wicket in the Border-Gavaskar Trophy. Pant shared the clip on Instagram, seemingly for a brand. Gavaskar had criticised Pant for his dismissal in the fourth Test of the series in December 2024, calling it a 'stupid shot.'
title: WATCH: Pant recreates Gavaskar's 'stupid, stupid, stupid' commentary

description: Yemen's Houthi rebels, backed by Iran, have launched three attacks within 48 hours on the USS Harry S. Truman carrier group in retaliation to US strikes in Yemen. These escalations, involving missiles and drones, follow a deadly US operation targeting Houthi leaders, risking further regional instability.
title: Iran-backed Houthis claim a third attack in 48 hours on US ships

description: Stock market recommendations: According to Mirae Asset Sharekhan, Trent is recommended for purchase between Rs 5140 and Rs 5165 with a target of Rs 5350, aided by a positive momentum indicator. Bharat Forge is suggested for buying between Rs 1065 and Rs 1085, targeting Rs 1300, also supported by a positive momentum indicator.
title: Top stocks to buy today: Stock recommendations for today
Aurangzeb tomb tension: Arson, stone-pelting in Nagpur, 50 arrested

description: During a 2024 visit, Donald Trump suggested Wayne Gretzky should run for Canadian prime minister, humorously proposing Canada could become a U.S. state. Gretzky declined, preferring to stay out of politics despite past endorsements of Conservative leaders. While the idea entertained many, it highlighted Trump's unconventional views on U.S.-Canada relations and elicited some concern among Canadian policymakers.
title: Donald Trump once urged Wayne Gretzky to run for the Prime Minister of Canada

description: Israeli airstrikes in Gaza targeted areas around Bureij, killing several Palestinians. Additional attacks in Lebanon and Syria resulted in more casualties, including children. The escalation endangers fragile ceasefires, with both sides accusing each other of violations. Mediators work towards a lasting truce amidst continued blockades and negotiations.
title: Israel conducts 'extensive strikes' in Gaza, Lebanon, Syria; over 40 killed

description: UBS has initiated coverage of BSE with a 'buy' rating, highlighting diverse revenue streams and potential margin improvement. Goldman Sachs has a 'sell' rating on Dixon Technologies due to the loss of PLI benefits. HSBC upgraded Tata Motors to 'buy', despite cutting the target price. Citi gives HPCL a 'buy' rating, while Elara Securities advises to accumulate Varun Beverages.
title: Stock recommendations by brokers for today

description: Rioting erupted in the Mahal area of Nagpur following a protest by VHP and Bajrang Dal demanding the removal of Aurangzeb's tomb. The situation escalated by evening, leading to a heavy police presence and use of tear gas. By midnight, the area remained tense and filled with fear, with signs of violence and several detentions.
title: Nagpur violence: Midnight silence follows hours of mayhem in Mahal’s historic quarters
At least 10 dead as Israel launches airstrikes in Gaza, Lebanon and Syria

description: India and China expressed mutual interest in fostering cooperation and strengthening relations following positive discussions between PM Modi and President Xi Jinping. Both countries aim to implement the understandings reached during their October meeting in Kazan, emphasizing development, revitalization, and the overall progress of their civilizations.
title: China welcomes PM Modi's positive remarks on ties

description: Maharashtra CM Devendra Fadnavis warns of strict action against anyone attempting to glorify Mughal emperor Aurangzeb. This statement comes amid controversy over Congress leader Harshvardhan Sapkal comparing Fadnavis to Aurangzeb, which has sparked political uproar and demands for action against Sapkal.
title: Devendra Fadnavis laments govt has to protect Aurangzeb's grave

description: Starlink faces a potential 3% spectrum tax on its adjusted gross revenue in India. This tax, alongside an 8% license fee, could increase service costs for the company. Discussions by Trai on pricing and taxes for satellite spectrum allocation are ongoing, with final recommendations expected soon.
title: Elon Musk's Starlink likely to face spectrum tax

description: US intelligence chief Tulsi Gabbard expressed concerns about persecution of minorities in Bangladesh and the global threat of Islamist terrorism. In a meeting with India's Defence Minister Rajnath Singh, she discussed the strategic security partnership and Singh urged the US to designate Sikhs For Justice as a terrorist organization.
title: US concerned about B'desh minorities, will defeat 'Islamist terror' globally: Tulsi

description: A seven-year-old girl from Ghaziabad was reported dead after allegedly eating food from a neighbor, Shanti Devi. However, an autopsy revealed she was raped and murdered, leading to her father's arrest. The father had tried to frame Shanti by claiming food poisoning. Police found his claims were false and arrested him for the heinous crime.
title: Food poisoning probe reveals Ghaziabad girl, 7, was raped and killed by dad on Holi

description: CCTV footage from the investigation into a fatal accident revealed that Pranshu Chauhan initially took the driver's seat but then moved to the front passenger seat at the insistence of Rakshit Chaurasiya. Chaurasiya then drove the car and later crashed into three two-wheelers, killing one woman and injuring seven others.
title: Vadodara car crash: 'Rakshit Chaurasiya may have insisted on driving'

description: Tesla facilities and vehicles in the US are facing protests and vandalism due to CEO Elon Musk's role in the Department of Government Efficiency. Some protests have led to arson at showrooms and charging stations. Jackron claimed to have infiltrated a protest, revealing Democrat-funded Facebook-organized protests. President Trump warned perpetrators, promising strict action.
title: ‘Mechanical engineer’ claims 'Facebook link' in Tesla protests, Elon Musk responds
